See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Registered trademark name for the African horned melon, Cucumis metaliferus (fam. Cucurbitaceae), a native of the Kalahari Desert introduced to New Zealand around 1920, the name invented by grower Sharyn Morris to combine Kiwi, 'an' (for its delicate banana flavour) and 'o' (as in the endings of other exotics such as pepino, babaco, tamarillo); also known as Mexican fruit salad, spiny cucumber and jelly melon.
