Quote:  The family of Cucumis metuliferus is alive and well in Kaukapakapa, North Auckland, but they could be classed as undesirables and possibly prohibited from travelling to the United States. Cucumis metuliferus is the botanical name for a relatively new development in New Zealand horticulture. it is the kiwano, sometimes known as horned melon, African horned cucumber, or jelly melon, and is thought to have originated in tropical Africa.
